Run your application with Score-P
---------------------------------

To run your application with Score-P just insert 'scorep --instrument' before
your actual compiler command, e.g. in your make file:
CC = scorep --instrument mpicc

After compiling run your binary as usual.

You can have a look on the trace file with the otf2_print tool:
otf2_print --anchor-file=scorep-***/traces.otf2


Useful Environment Variables:
-----------------------------

SCOREP_ENABLE_PROFILING:
 - enable profiling
   (default: false)

SCOREP_ENABLE_TRACING:
 - enable tracing
   (default: true)

SCOREP_TOTAL_MEMORY:
 - total memory in bytes for the measurement system, excluding trace memory
   (default: 1200k)

SCOREP_PAGE_SIZE:
 - SCOREP_TOTAL_MEMORY will be split up into pages of size SCOREP_PAGE_SIZE.
   (default: 8k)
